<div id="review_127276327" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/127276327" />
    <a title="Dalia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3813585-dalia"><img alt="Dalia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1424972982p2/3813585.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/127276327?book_show_action=true">Oct 21, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dalia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dalia" href="/user/show/3813585-dalia">Dalia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780956003805" href="/book/show/6351531-driving-over-lemons">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer127276327" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14449924167682669707">I picked this up in the travel guide section at the library when I started planning my trip to Portugal. I was suprised to see a book like this in that section but I guess its not hefty enough for a memoir so there really isn&apos;t a proper home for it. I know understand why Cooking with Fernet Branca was made- these gringo moves to peasant territory books are so formulaic- this even has the requisite recipe for &quot;poorman&apos;s potatoes&quot;...... No real reason to read this, zero drama, zero suprises....</span>
  <span id="freeText14449924167682669707" style="display:none">I picked this up in the travel guide section at the library when I started planning my trip to Portugal. I was suprised to see a book like this in that section but I guess its not hefty enough for a memoir so there really isn't a proper home for it. I know understand why Cooking with Fernet Branca was made- these gringo moves to peasant territory books are so formulaic- this even has the requisite recipe for "poorman's potatoes"...... No real reason to read this, zero drama, zero suprises....</span>
